article.headline: Arkansas Tech , UMKC 90
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Dane Brumagin scored 22 points and Reggie Hamilton 17 to rally UMKC to a 90-82 victory over Arkansas Tech on Saturday. Hamilton's 3-pointer with 2:03 left put UMKC (2-3) up 79-76 for their first lead in the second half as part of an 18-0 run. Jeremiah Hartsock had 15 points for the Kangaroos, but only four in the second half. Arkansas Tech (3-1), a NCAA Division II school, went more than four minutes late in the game without a point as it had its 12-point lead erased with eight minutes left. Troy Marcus, who had scored just 25 points in the Wonder Boys first three games, led Arkansas Tech with 22 points, while Terrance Whiters contributed 18 points. UMKC committed a season-high 26 turnovers, which Arkansas Tech converted into 30 points. Arkansas Tech coach Mark Downey was ejected after drawing his second technical foul with 10:24 left in the opening half. When Downey was seen at the end of the auditorium signaling the bench with 2:51 left in the game, Arkansas State was issued another technical. The Kangaroos, who had lost road games to nationally ranked Kansas and Arizona, trailed by as many as 13 points in the first half, trailing 17-4 after eight minutes. UMKC, however, scored 12 unanswered points with Brent Stephens, who finished with 12 points, and Brumagin hitting 3-pointers. The Kangaroos led by four points with 1:02 left in the half. The Wonder Boys, however, made two steals and converted them into two Whiters treys in the final 10 seconds to take a 38-36 advantage at half.
